Hello, first of all thank you for making such an useful thing, it makes control stuff so simple  <img class="smilies" src="http://love2d.org/forums/images/smilies/ms-awesome.png" width="16" height="16" alt=":awesome:" title="I'M SO HAPPY I COULD SHIT A RAINBOW RIGHT NOW"> <br>I just wanted to point out a bug in the latest (1.3) version:<br><br>The controls are reset in line 62<div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>for k,v in pairs(control) do if type(v)~="table" then control[k] = false end end</code></pre></div>But it used to clear only booleans in an older version I had<div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>for k,v in pairs(hold) do if type(v)=="boolean" then hold[k] = nil end end</code></pre></div>So now it turns anything to 'false'! Including the controlPressed and controlReleased functions you're supposed to be able to assign. It's easy to fix, but I thought I should point it out.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=133995">bunny_</a> — Thu Sep 05, 2013 6:04 pm</p><hr />
